article_title: Today’s Top Supply Chain and Logistics News From WSJ
article_text:
Sign up: With one click, get this newsletter delivered to your inbox.

Energy markets are whipsawing freight railroads. Steep declines in coal, crude and frac carloads are wiping away any benefits Union Pacific Corp. saw from lower fuel costs in the fourth quarter several times over, the WSJ’s Laura Stevens and Betsy Morris report. The dismal energy environment helped send UP’s earnings down 22% from the same quarter a year ago, and there’s little help on the way from key carloads. With coal inventory levels now 39 days...
